# Project Database Rules — NON-NEGOTIABLE

## 1. Production Database Targeting
All content intended for the published/live site (exam questions, allied questions,
imaging questions, flashcards, content items) MUST be written to the PRODUCTION database.

- Use `PROD_DATABASE_URL` for production writes
- Use `DATABASE_URL` for development/local reads and writes
- All seed scripts and content generators default to `PROD_DATABASE_URL || DATABASE_URL`

## 2. Centralized Database Module
All database connections MUST go through `server/db.ts`. Never create standalone
`new pg.Pool({ connectionString: process.env.DATABASE_URL })` instances in server files.

- `getDevPool()` — returns the development database pool
- `getProdPool()` — returns the production database pool
- `getPool(target)` — returns pool for "production" or "development"
- Seed scripts (script/, scripts/) use `process.env.PROD_DATABASE_URL || process.env.DATABASE_URL` directly

## 3. Logging Requirements
Every bulk insert operation MUST:
- Log which database it targets BEFORE writing (use `logDatabaseTarget()`)
- Log the row count AFTER writing (use `logRowCount()`)

## 4. Sync Protocol
When dev has content not yet in production:
- Use the admin panel at /admin/database-status to check counts
- Use the one-click sync button (idempotent, uses ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING)
- Never manually copy data without conflict handling

## 5. Environment Variables
- `DATABASE_URL` — Development/default database
- `PROD_DATABASE_URL` — Production database (if separate from dev)
- When `PROD_DATABASE_URL` is not set, both pools point to `DATABASE_URL`

## 6. Dev-Only Writes = Failed Task
Writing content for the live site to only the dev database is a FAILED TASK
unless explicitly requested by the developer for testing purposes.
